msgstr ""
"Many parameters have ``PRIMARY`` in their names because some GMT map frames ("
"especially the ``fancy`` type frames) use different settings to render "
"primary gridlines (and ticks) and secondary gridlines (and ticks). In our "
"case, we only set the primary main gridlines and omit the secondary "
"gridlines. You can also change to a ``fancy`` type map frame and specify the "
"style of secondary gridlines (by setting the parameters with ``SECONDARY`` "
"in their name) to see what the figure looks like!"

